== Nearby Cities ==
The following is a list of Lake Charles' nearby cities:
*[[Moss Bluff, Louisiana|Moss Bluff]] - suburb of 10,535 north of Lake Charles via [[U.S. Highway 171]]. Moss Bluff is the fastest-growing area in the greater city{{Fact|date=February 2007}}, and predicted to be the largest satellite in the near-future.
*[[LeBleu Settlement, Louisiana|LeBleu Settlement]] - extensive area spanning over [[Calcasieu Parish|Calcasieu]] and [[Jefferson Davis Parish|Jefferson Davis]] parishes, adjacent to Moss Bluff and Iowa.
*[[Iowa, Louisiana|Iowa]] - small city of 2,663 east of Lake Charles.
*[[Carlyss, Louisiana|Carlyss]] - town of 4,049 located between Sulphur and [[Hackberry, Louisiana|Hackberry]]. Carlyss is also one of the fastest growing communities in Calcasieu parish{{Fact|date=February 2007}}.
*[[Sulphur, Louisiana|Sulphur]] - city of 22,512 located to the west of Lake Charles via [[Interstate 10 in Louisiana|Interstate 10]] and [[U.S. Highway 90]].
*[[Westlake, Louisiana|Westlake]] - suburb of 4,668 located directly west of downtown Lake Charles across from the [[Calcasieu River]] and [[Lake Charles (body of water)|Lake Charles]].

[[Image:Hiberniatower.JPG|thumb|right|350px|[[Capital One Tower (Lake Charles)|Capital One Tower]] in downtown Lake Charles after [[Hurricane Rita]]]]

